    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A bright, natural red volcanic pigment originally mined at Pozzuoli near Naples, Italy. It was used by the Romans and others as a paint pigment, becoming popular for fresco paintings because it dried quickly to a hard impenetrable surface like cement.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
